{
  "texts": [
    "Even if a model can answer questions consistently using both internal and external knowledge, errors may still occur during multi-step reasoning.",
    "To address the issue of faulty reasoning, we propose improvements from two perspectives: • Double-Checking the Reasoning Process.",
    "First, we aim to verify that each statement in our reasoning process is backed by evidence.",
    "To achieve this, we invoke the NLI model 𝑓 to assess the groundedness of each statement 𝑠 𝑖 in the LLM output 𝑦.",
    "This will help determine which statements are supported by external references 𝐷 𝑞 = {𝑑 1, 𝑑 2,...} and which ones aren't."
  ]
}